dataIdInfo.idAbs: The dataset represents the Common Operational Data (COD) for Admin3 (Aldeia/Community) boundaries of Timor-Leste (East Timor). Each administrative unit contains the p-code and name.

Consts.useLimit: See the COD/FOD Registry Terms of Use. This does not replace any terms of use information provided with the dataset.

dataLineage.statement:
Layer was downloaded as a shapefile by ITOS from HDX. It was then analyzed by ITOS for errors. Those errors were corrected and then the layer was sent back to UNOCHA as a feature class within a file geodatabase.
The following was found and fixed by ITOS: 1. Created and populated reference name field. 2. Admin2 name "Aileu vila" and Admin3 names "Acadiru hun", "Abat oan", "Balibo vila", "Belulik leten" were made Proper Case. 3. 14 Admin3 features with identical names and p-codes have been merged into single mulitpart features. 4. 2 Admin3 units named "Maina II" existed in Admin2 "Lautem". As instructed by UNOCHA, the northern Admin3 unit has been renamed "Maina I". 5. Some name spellings were changed to make names consistent among layers: Admin1 name "Lautem" was changed to "Lautém". Admin2 names were changed from "Vemase" to "Vemasse", "Lautem" to "Lautém", "Pante Macasar" to "Pante Macassar", "Watulari" to "Uato-Lari".
NOTE: Some names have slashes, meaning there may be alternate names that need to be separated and placed in altName fields
